The paper deals with semirings and their properties, which are typically studied in the formal language theory (cs.FL) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. The Kleene theorem mentioned in the abstract is a fundamental result in automata theory, which is a subfield of formal language theory. The paper also discusses the Conway identities, which are related to the algebraic structure of semirings and can be studied in the sub-categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and symbolic computation (cs.SC). Finally, the paper introduces a generalization of Conway semirings called iteration semirings, which can be studied in the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT).
